ents\nremoves newlines and line feeds keeping\nremoves last semicolon from last property','',55,NULL,'Phalcon\\Assets\\FilterInterface'),(256,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Assets\\Filters','Jsmin',0,0,0,'assets/filters/jsmin.c','Deletes the characters which are insignificant to JavaScript. Comments will be removed. Tabs will be\nreplaced with spaces. Carriage returns will be replaced with linefeeds.\nMost spaces and linefeeds will be removed.','',55,NULL,'Phalcon\\Assets\\FilterInterface'),(257,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Assets\\Resource','Css',0,0,0,'assets/resource/css.c','Represents CSS resources','',51,'Phalcon\\Assets\\Resource',NULL),(258,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http','Request',0,0,0,'http/request.c','<p>Encapsulates request information for easy and secure access from application controllers.</p>\n\n<p>The request object is a simple value object that is passed between the dispatcher and controller classes.\nIt packages the HTTP request environment.</p>','$request = new Phalcon\\Http\\Request();\nif ($request->isPost() == true) {\n	if ($request->isAjax() == true) {\n		echo \'Request was made using POST and AJAX\';\n	}\n}',171,NULL,'Phalcon\\Http\\RequestInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(259,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http','Cookie',0,0,0,'http/cookie.c','Provide OO wrappers to manage a HTTP cookie','',142,NULL,'Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(260,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http','Response',0,0,0,'http/response.c','Part of the HTTP cycle is return responses to the clients.\nPhalcon\\HTTP\\Response is the Phalcon component responsible to achieve this task.\nHTTP responses are usually composed by headers and body.','$response = new Phalcon\\Http\\Response();\n$response->setStatusCode(200, \"OK\");\n$response->setContent(\"<html><body>Hello</body></html>\");\n$response->send();',137,NULL,'Phalcon\\Http\\ResponseInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(261,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http\\Request','File',0,0,0,'http/request/file.c','Provides OO wrappers to the $_FILES superglobal','class PostsController extends \\Phalcon\\Mvc\\Controller\n{\n\n	public function uploadAction()\n	{\n		//Check if the user has uploaded files\n		if ($this->request->hasFiles() == true) {\n			//Print the real file names and their sizes\n			foreach ($this->request->getUploadedFiles() as $file){\n				echo $file->getName(), \" \", $file->getSize(), \"\\n\";\n			}\n		}\n	}\n\n}',99,'SplFileInfo','Phalcon\\Http\\Request\\FileInterface'),(262,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http\\Response','Cookies',0,0,0,'http/response/cookies.c','This class is a bag to manage the cookies\nA cookies bag is automatically registered as part of the \'response\' service in the DI','',77,NULL,'Phalcon\\Http\\Response\\CookiesInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(263,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Http\\Response','Headers',0,0,0,'http/response/headers.c','This class is a bag to manage the response headers','',68,NULL,'Phalcon\\Http\\Response\\HeadersInterface'),(264,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Queue','Beanstalk',0,0,0,'queue/beanstalk.c','Class to access the beanstalk queue service.\nPartially implements the protocol version 1.2','',110,NULL,NULL),(265,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Queue\\Beanstalk','Job',0,0,0,'queue/beanstalk/job.c','Represents a job in a beanstalk queue','',71,NULL,NULL),(266,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','View',0,0,0,'mvc/view.c','Phalcon\\Mvc\\View is a class for working with the \"view\" portion of the model-view-controller pattern.\nThat is, it exists to help keep the view script separate from the model and controller scripts.\nIt provides a system of helpers, output filters, and variable escaping.','//Setting views directory\n$view = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\View();\n$view->setViewsDir(\'app/views/\');\n\n$view->start();\n//Shows recent posts view (app/views/posts/recent.phtml)\n$view->render(\'posts\', \'recent\');\n$view->finish();\n\n//Printing views output\necho $view->getContent();',212,'Phalcon\\DI\\Injectable','Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Phalcon\\Mvc\\ViewInterface'),(267,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Url',0,0,0,'mvc/url.c','This components aids in the generation of: URIs, URLs and Paths','\n//Generate a URL appending the URI to the base URI\necho $url->get(\'products/edit/1\');\n\n//Generate a URL for a predefined route\necho $url->get(array(\'for\' => \'blog-post\', \'title\' => \'some-cool-stuff\', \'year\' => \'2012\'));',95,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\UrlInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(268,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Model',0,1,0,'mvc/model.c','<p>Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model connects business objects and database tables to create\na persistable domain model where logic and data are presented in one wrapping.\nIts an implementation of the object-relational mapping (ORM).</p>\n\n<p>A model represents the information (data) of the application and the rules to manipulate that data.\nModels are primarily used for managing the rules of interaction with a corresponding database table.\nIn most cases, each table in your database will correspond to one model in your application.\nThe bulk of your applications business logic will be concentrated in the models.</p>\n\n<p>Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model is the first ORM written in C-language for PHP, giving to developers high performance\nwhen interacting with databases while is also easy to use.</p>','\n$robot = new Robots();\n$robot->type = \'mechanical\';\n$robot->name = \'Astro Boy\';\n$robot->year = 1952;\nif ($robot->save() == false) {\n echo \"Umh, We can store robots: \";\n foreach ($robot->getMessages() as $message) {\n   echo $message;\n }\n} else {\n echo \"Great, a new robot was saved successfully!\";\n}',397,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\ModelInterface,Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\ResultInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Serializable'),(269,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Micro',0,0,0,'mvc/micro.c','With Phalcon you can create \"Micro-Framework like\" applications. By doing this, you only need to\nwrite a minimal amount of code to create a PHP application. Micro applications are suitable\nto small applications, APIs and prototypes in a practical way.','\n$app = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro();\n\n$app->get(\'/say/welcome/{name}\', function ($name) {\n   echo \"<h1>Welcome $name!</h1>\";\n});\n\n$app->handle();',228,'Phalcon\\DI\\Injectable','Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,ArrayAccess'),(270,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Application',0,0,0,'mvc/application.c','This component encapsulates all the complex operations behind instantiating every component\nneeded and integrating it with the rest to allow the MVC pattern to operate as desired.','\nclass Application extends \\Phalcon\\Mvc\\Application\n{\n\n	/\\**\n	 * Register the services here to make them general or register\n	 * in the ModuleDefinition to make them module-specific\n	 *\\/\n	protected function _registerServices()\n	{\n\n	}\n\n	/\\**\n	 * This method registers all the modules in the application\n	 *\\/\n	public function main()\n	{\n		$this->registerModules(array(\n			\'frontend\' => array(\n				\'className\' => \'Multiple\\Frontend\\Module\',\n				\'path\' => \'../apps/frontend/Module.php\'\n			),\n			\'backend\' => array(\n				\'className\' => \'Multiple\\Backend\\Module\',\n				\'path\' => \'../apps/backend/Module.php\'\n			)\n		));\n	}\n}\n\n$application = new Application();\n$application->main();',134,'Phalcon\\DI\\Injectable','Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(271,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Collection',0,0,0,'mvc/collection.c','This component implements a high level abstraction for NoSQL databases which\nworks with documents','',166,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\CollectionInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Serializable'),(272,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Controller',0,1,0,'mvc/controller.c','Every application controller should extend this class that encapsulates all the controller functionality\n\nThe controllers provide the flow between models and views. Controllers are responsible\nfor processing the incoming requests from the web browser, interrogating the models for data,\nand passing that data on to the views for presentation.','\nclass PeopleController extends \\Phalcon\\Mvc\\Controller\n{\n\n //This action will be executed by default\n public function indexAction()\n {\n\n }\n\n public function findAction()\n {\n\n }\n\n public function saveAction()\n {\n  //Forwards flow to the index action\n  return $this->dispatcher->forward(array(\'controller\' => \'people\', \'action\' => \'index\'));\n }\n\n}',76,'Phalcon\\DI\\Injectable','Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Phalcon\\Mvc\\ControllerInterface'),(273,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Collection','Document',0,0,0,'mvc/collection/document.c','This component allows Phalcon\\Mvc\\Collection to return rows without an associated entity.\nThis objects implements the ArrayAccess interface to allow access the object as object->x or array[x].','',82,NULL,'ArrayAccess'),(274,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Collection','Manager',0,0,0,'mvc/collection/manager.c','This components controls the initialization of models, keeping record of relations\nbetween the different models of the application.\n\nA CollectionManager is injected to a model via a Dependency Injector Container such as Phalcon\\DI.','$di = new Phalcon\\DI();\n\n$di->set(\'collectionManager\', function(){\n     return new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Collection\\Manager();\n});\n\n$robot = new Robots($di);',96,NULL,'Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\Mvc\\Collection\\ManagerInterface'),(275,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc','Dispatcher',0,0,0,'mvc/dispatcher.c','Dispatching is the process of taking the request object, extracting the module name,\ncontroller name, action name, and optional parameters contained in it, and then\ninstantiating a controller and calling an action of that controller.','\n$di = new Phalcon\\DI();\n\n$dispatcher = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Dispatcher();\n\n $dispatcher->setDI($di);\n\n$dispatcher->setControllerName(\'posts\');\n$dispatcher->setActionName(\'index\');\n$dispatcher->setParams(array());\n\n$controller = $dispatcher->dispatch();',92,'Phalcon\\Dispatcher','Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Phalcon\\DispatcherInterface,Phalcon\\Mvc\\DispatcherInterface'),(276,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Row',0,0,0,'mvc/model/row.c','This component allows Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model to return rows without an associated entity.\nThis objects implements the ArrayAccess interface to allow access the object as object->x or array[x].','',81,NULL,'ArrayAccess,Countable,Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\ResultInterface'),(277,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Query',0,0,0,'mvc/model/query.c','This class takes a PHQL intermediate representation and executes it.','\n$phql = \"SELECT c.price*0.16 AS taxes, c.* FROM Cars AS c JOIN Brands AS b\n         WHERE b.name = :name: ORDER BY c.name\";\n\n$result = $manager->executeQuery($phql, array(\n  \'name\' => \'Lamborghini\'\n));\n\nforeach ($result as $row) {\n  echo \"Name: \", $row->cars->name, \"\\n\";\n  echo \"Price: \", $row->cars->price, \"\\n\";\n  echo \"Taxes: \", $row->taxes, \"\\n\";\n}',202,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\QueryInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(278,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro','Collection',0,0,0,'mvc/micro/collection.c','Groups Micro-Mvc handlers as controllers','\n$app = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro();\n\n$collection = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro\\Collection();\n\n$collection->setHandler(new PostsController());\n\n$collection->get(\'/posts/edit/{id}\', \'edit\');\n\n$app->mount($collection);',91,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro\\CollectionInterface'),(279,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro','Exception',0,0,0,'mvc/micro/exception.c','Exceptions thrown in Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro will use this class','',35,'Phalcon\\Exception',NULL),(280,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Micro','LazyLoader',0,0,0,'mvc/micro/lazyloader.c','Lazy-Load of handlers for Mvc\\Micro using auto-loading','',57,NULL,NULL),(281,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Criteria',0,0,0,'mvc/model/criteria.c','This class allows to build the array parameter required by Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model::find\nand Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model::findFirst using an object-oriented interface','$robots = Robots::query()\n   ->where(\"type = :type:\")\n   ->andWhere(\"year < 2000\")\n   ->bind(array(\"type\" => \"mechanical\"))\n   ->order(\"name\")\n   ->execute();',155,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\CriteriaInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface'),(282,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Manager',0,0,0,'mvc/model/manager.c','This components controls the initialization of models, keeping record of relations\nbetween the different models of the application.\n\nA ModelsManager is injected to a model via a Dependency Injector/Services Container such as Phalcon\\DI.','$di = new Phalcon\\DI();\n\n$di->set(\'modelsManager\', function() {\n     return new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Manager();\n});\n\n$robot = new Robots($di);',318,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\ManagerInterface,Phalcon\\DI\\InjectionAwareInterface,Phalcon\\Events\\EventsAwareInterface'),(283,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Message',0,0,0,'mvc/model/message.c','Encapsulates validation info generated before save/delete records fails','use Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Message as Message;\n\n class Robots extends Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\n {\n\n   public function beforeSave()\n   {\n     if ($this->name == \'Peter\') {\n       $text = \"A robot cannot be named Peter\";\n       $field = \"name\";\n       $type = \"InvalidValue\";\n       $code = 103;\n       $message = new Message($text, $field, $type, $code);\n       $this->appendMessage($message);\n    }\n  }\n\n}',108,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\MessageInterface'),(284,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Relation',0,0,0,'mvc/model/relation.c','This class represents a relationship between two models','',80,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\RelationInterface'),(285,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model','Transaction',0,0,0,'mvc/model/transaction.c','Transactions are protective blocks where SQL statements are only permanent if they can\nall succeed as one atomic action. Phalcon\\Transaction is intended to be used with Phalcon_Model_Base.\nPhalcon Transactions should be created using Phalcon\\Transaction\\Manager.','try {\n\n $manager = new Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Transaction\\Manager();\n\n $transaction = $manager->get();\n\n $robot = new Robots();\n $robot->setTransaction($transaction);\n $robot->name = \'WALLE\';\n $robot->created_at = date(\'Y-m-d\');\n if ($robot->save() == false) {\n   $transaction->rollback(\"Can\'t save robot\");\n }\n\n $robotPart = new RobotParts();\n $robotPart->setTransaction($transaction);\n $robotPart->type = \'head\';\n if ($robotPart->save() == false) {\n   $transaction->rollback(\"Can\'t save robot part\");\n }\n\n $transaction->commit();\n\n} catch(Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Transaction\\Failed $e) {\n echo \'Failed, reason: \', $e->getMessage();\n}',110,NULL,'Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\TransactionInterface'),(286,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Query','Lang',0,1,0,'mvc/model/query/lang.c','PHQL is implemented as a parser (written in C) that translates syntax in\nthat of the target RDBMS. It allows Phalcon to offer a unified SQL language to\nthe developer, while internally doing all the work of translating PHQL\ninstructions to the most optimal SQL instructions depending on the\nRDBMS type associated with a model.\n\nTo achieve the highest performance possible, we wrote a parser that uses\nthe same technology as SQLite. This technology provides a small in-memory\nparser with a very low memory footprint that is also thread-safe.','$intermediate = Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Query\\Lang::parsePHQL(\"SELECT r.* FROM Robots r LIMIT 10\");',63,NULL,NULL),(287,'1.3.3','Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Validator','Url',0,0,0,'mvc/model/validator/url.c','Allows to validate if a field has a url format','use Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\\Validator\\Url as UrlValidator;\n\nclass Posts extends Phalcon\\Mvc\\Model\n{\n\n public function validation()\n {\n     $this->validate(new UrlValidator(arr